# The vendored Clojure sources are kept byte-identical to upstream so that
#     git diff clojure-1.12.5 -- src test
# shows exactly our changes and nothing else.
#
# 15 upstream files are stored with CRLF (epl-v10.html, Sequential.java, ISeq.java, ...). This
# machine has core.autocrlf=input, which would normalize them to LF when git hashes the working
# tree, making those files diff as fully rewritten. -text disables all EOL conversion.
#
# Consequence: if you edit one of those CRLF files with an editor that saves LF, its diff will
# balloon to the whole file. Keep CRLF in the files that already have it.
* -text
